eZ publish 3 installation ( BETA )
----------------------------------

Required software to run eZ publish 3:

You need to have apache and php installed.
PHP needs to have compiled in support for either MySQL or PostgreSQL. 
For image conversion support you need to have GD compiled in PHP or
ImageMagick installed on your system. 

eZ publish 3 beta 2 is tested on these versions:
apache-1.3.27
php-4.1.2 

Please report other versions eZ publish runs successfully on to beta@ez.no.

eZ publish instalation:
-----------------------
1. Unpack ezpublish-2.9-3.tar.gz in httproot folder
2. cd <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/
3. Run $ bin/modfix.sh

Database setup:
--------------
For postgresql:
1. createdb <name_of_database>
2. psql ezpublish_demo < <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/kernel/sql/postgresql/kernel_clean.sql
For mysql:
1. mysqladmin -u <user> -p create <name_of_database>
2. mysql -u <user> -p  <name_of_database> <  <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/kernel/sql/mysql/kernel_clean.sql

Configure eZ publish:
--------------------
1. Open <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/settings/site.ini with editor and setup correct [DatabaseSettings]
You need to chose what db implementation you will use, hostname of db server to connect to, 
db user name, db user password, and db name.
[DatabaseSettings]
# Use either ezmysql or ezpostgresql
DatabaseImplementation=ezpostgresql
# Name of server to connect to 
Server=localhost
# DB user name
User=sp
# DB Password
Password=sp
# database name you have created on previous step
Database=sp_demo

Demo data:
----------
You can setup demodata for eZ publish. But this aviable only for MySQL.
For that you need to create database and insert demodata from demokernel.sql
1. mysqladmin -u <user> -p create <name_of_database>
2. mysql -u <user> -p  <name_of_database> <  <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/kernel/sql/mysql/demokernel.sql
3. cd <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/ 
4. tar xfvz var.tgz 
5. bin/modfix.sh



Virtualhost setup:
------------------
You can use eZ publish with a virtualhost setup. When using 
a virtualhost you don't need to specify the index.php in the URL.
Below is a sample configuration for virtualhost setup.

<VirtualHost 10.0.0.1>
 <Directory <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/>
       Options FollowSymLinks Indexes ExecCGI
       AllowOverride None 
  </Directory>

  RewriteEngine On 
  RewriteRule !\.(gif|css|jpg|png)$ <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/index.php

  ServerAdmin root@localhost
  DocumentRoot <httproot>/ezpublish-2.9-3/
  ServerName 10.0.0.1
</VirtualHost>


That's it,

Enjoy !

- eZ publish team